[1] Mexico (San Luis Potosi)
Date: Mon 21 Oct 2013
Source: Pulso [in Spanish, machine trans., summ., edited]
http://pulsoslp.com.mx/2013/10/21/confirma-salud-segundo-caso-de-colera-en-slp-analizan-muestras-en-la-capital/


The secretary of health in the state of San Luis Potosi, Francisco Javier Posadas Robledo, has revealed the confirmation of a 2nd case of cholera in the Huasteca Potosina region, also in an adult, and that there are suspected cases in the capital [San Luis Potosi] but none are confirmed as cholera.

He mentioned that about 3 per cent of all diarrheal episodes were sampled and "we have tested around 2000 samples in the past 2 months and apart from these 2 cases, none produced a positive result for cholera". He added that it is important to strengthen the preventive measures.

[byline: Lucia Torres]

